net.sf.opensftp
Class SftpUtilFactory

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtilFactory

public class SftpUtilFactory
extends java.lang.Object

Factory that implements the following algorithm to dynamically select a SftpUtil implementation class to instantiate a Singleton object for.

  • Use the implementation class specified through the /opensftp-config/sftputil-impl/@type node in the opensftp-config.xml configuration file.
  • Use the implementation class specified through the net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtil system property.
  • Use the implementation class specified through the first and only effective call to setSftpUtilClassName(String).
  • Otherwise, use the default implementation class SftpUtil.

NOTE: Among the above approaches, one should effectivly set an SftpUtil implementation class name, otherwise, the flow goes to the next one. It's not a effective set if you specify a class which doesn't exist in the classpath or doesn't implement SftpUtil at all.

setSftpUtilClassName

public static void setSftpUtilClassName(java.lang.String name)
Set the name of the SftpUtil implementation class with the specified name.

This method can be used to set the name of the SftpUtil implementation class programmatically rather than via configuration file or system property.

A call to this method is effective only when the following conditions are all met.

  • The /opensftp-config/sftputil-impl/@type node in the opensftp-config.xml configuration file was not or not effectively set. It's not a effective set if you specify a class which doesn't exist in the classpath or doesn't implement SftpUtil at all.
  • The net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtil system property was not or not effectively set.
  • No previous call to getSftpUtilClassName().
  • No previous call to getSftpUtil().
  • The class identified by the specified name exists in the classpath and implements SftpUtil.
  • No previous effective call to this method.

Parameters:
name - Name of the SftpUtil implementation class to set
